{
  "doc_id": "57",
  "text": "Compounds containing C-F bonds are rarely found in nature, in contrast to the abundant fluoride anions [1, [CITATION_1] . The fluoride ion is extensively hydrated and therefore relatively unreactive as a nucleophile, inhibiting C-F bond formation in nature. However, fluorinated organic compounds play an important role and are widely used in the synthesis of pharmaceuticals and agrochemicals due to their favourable chemical and biological properties.",
